Interface Dictionary<K,V>

public interface Dictionary<K,V>
extends Collection<K>

Generic dictionary interface. "One striking design choice of the Java language designers was the exclusion of map from the collections hierarchy." (Brad Long: "Towards the design of a set-based Java collections framework," ACM SIGSOFT SEN, Volume 35 Issue 6, November 2010). In the iKor Collection Framework, dictionaries (a.k.a. maps) are also collections.

Author:
Fernando Berzal
